==English==
===Noun===
'''indicator'''
# a [[pointer]] or [[index]] that [[indicate]]s something
# a [[meter]] or [[gauge]]; the [[needle]] or [[dial]] on such a meter
#{{chemistry}} any of many substances, such as [[litmus]], used to indicate the [[concentration]] of a [[substance]], or the [[degree]] of a [[reaction]]
#(''ecology'') a [[plant]] or [[animal]] whose [[presence]] is [[indicative]] of some specific [[environment]]
#(''economics'') a [[measure]], such as [[unemployment]] [[rate]], which can be used to [[predict]] [[economic]] [[trend]]s
# a [[trafficator]]

